TITLE: Basic Proxy Usage Example in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a simple Proxy implementation that adds logging to property access operations on an object. The proxy intercepts 'get' operations on the target object, logs the property name being accessed, and returns the corresponding value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/optimizing-proxies.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const target = {};
const callTracer = new Proxy(target, {
  get: (target, name, receiver) => {
    console.log(`get was called for: ${name}`);
    return target[name];
  }
});

callTracer.property = 'value';
console.log(callTracer.property);
// get was called for: property
// value
```

