TITLE: Using String.prototype.matchAll with named capture groups in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how String.prototype.matchAll works with named capture groups, demonstrating how to access both the full match and the captured groups in a simple for-of loop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/features/string-matchall.md#2025-04-10_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const string = 'Favorite GitHub repos: tc39/ecma262 v8/v8.dev';
const regex = /\b(?<owner>[a-z0-9]+)\/(?<repo>[a-z0-9\.]+)\b/g;
for (const match of string.matchAll(regex)) {
  console.log(`${match[0]} at ${match.index} with '${match.input}'`);
  console.log(`â†’ owner: ${match.groups.owner}`);
  console.log(`â†’ repo: ${match.groups.repo}`);
}

// Output:
//
// tc39/ecma262 at 23 with 'Favorite GitHub repos: tc39/ecma262 v8/v8.dev'
// â†’ owner: tc39
// â†’ repo: ecma262
// v8/v8.dev at 36 with 'Favorite GitHub repos: tc39/ecma262 v8/v8.dev'
// â†’ owner: v8
// â†’ repo: v8.dev
```

