TITLE: Implementing Synchronous Lock Method
DESCRIPTION: Shows the implementation of a blocking lock method that can only be called from a worker thread using Atomics.compareExchange and Atomics.wait.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/features/atomics.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
lock() {
  while (true) {
    const oldValue = Atomics.compareExchange(this.i32a, AsyncLock.INDEX,
                        /* old value >>> */  AsyncLock.UNLOCKED,
                        /* new value >>> */  AsyncLock.LOCKED);
    if (oldValue == AsyncLock.UNLOCKED) {
      return;
    }
    Atomics.wait(this.i32a, AsyncLock.INDEX,
                 AsyncLock.LOCKED); // <<< expected value at start
  }
}
```

