TITLE: Stream Processing with Async Iteration
DESCRIPTION: Modern implementation using async iteration (for await...of) to process stream data chunks more elegantly with proper error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/fast-async.md#2025-04-10_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const http = require('http');

http.createServer(async (req, res) => {
  try {
    let body = '';
    req.setEncoding('utf8');
    for await (const chunk of req) {
      body += chunk;
    }
    res.write(body);
    res.end();
  } catch {
    res.statusCode = 500;
    res.end();
  }
}).listen(1337);
```

