TITLE: Using Iterator.reduce() Method in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: The reduce() method applies a reducer function to each value in the iterator, accumulating a single result. This example counts blog posts with the 'security' tag by reducing an iterator of tag names.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/features/iterator-helpers.md#2025-04-10_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Select the list of blog posts from a blog archive page.
const posts = document.querySelectorAll('li:not(header li)');

// Get list of tags for all posts.
const tagLists = posts.values().flatMap((x) => x.querySelectorAll('.tag').values());

// Get text context for each tag in the list.
const tags = tagLists.map((x) => x.textContent);

// Counts posts with security tag.
const count = tags.reduce((sum , value) => sum + (value === 'security' ? 1 : 0), 0);
console.log(count);
```

