TITLE: Recursive Fibonacci Implementation in WebAssembly
DESCRIPTION: WebAssembly implementation of Fibonacci function using tail calls with return_call instruction, demonstrating proper tail call optimization in WebAssembly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/wasm-tail-call.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: wasm
CODE:
```
(func $fib_rec (param $n i32) (param $a i32) (param $b i32) (result i32)
  (if (i32.eqz (local.get $n))
    (then (return (local.get $a)))
    (else
      (return_call $fib_rec
        (i32.sub (local.get $n) (i32.const 1))
        (local.get $b)
        (i32.add (local.get $a) (local.get $b))
      )
    )
  )
)

(func $fib (param $n i32) (result i32)
  (call $fib_rec (local.get $n) (i32.const 0) (i32.const 1))
)
```

