TITLE: Implementing custom Math.random function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows a custom implementation of Math.random used in the async-fs benchmark. It uses a deterministic algorithm to generate pseudo-random numbers for consistent results across runs. The function updates a 'seed' variable on each call, which becomes a performance bottleneck in the V8 engine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/mutable-heap-number.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
let seed;
Math.random = (function() {
  return function () {
    seed = ((seed + 0x7ed55d16) + (seed << 12))  & 0xffffffff;
    seed = ((seed ^ 0xc761c23c) ^ (seed >>> 19)) & 0xffffffff;
    seed = ((seed + 0x165667b1) + (seed << 5))   & 0xffffffff;
    seed = ((seed + 0xd3a2646c) ^ (seed << 9))   & 0xffffffff;
    seed = ((seed + 0xfd7046c5) + (seed << 3))   & 0xffffffff;
    seed = ((seed ^ 0xb55a4f09) ^ (seed >>> 16)) & 0xffffffff;
    return (seed & 0xfffffff) / 0x10000000;
  };
})();
```

