DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows a C function for computing Fibonacci numbers using JSPI to perform addition via JavaScript Promises. It demonstrates how to use the EM_ASYNC_JS macro to integrate JavaScript code within C.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/jspi.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
long promiseFib(long x) {
 if (x == 0)
   return 0;
 if (x == 1)
   return 1;
 return promiseAdd(promiseFib(x - 1), promiseFib(x - 2));
}
