TITLE: Specification-Compliant Class Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Detailed implementation showing the actual behavior of private fields according to the specification.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/faster-class-features.md#2025-04-10_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class A {
  constructor() {
    // What the %AddPrivateField() call roughly translates to:
    const _a = %PrivateSymbol('#a')
    if (_a in this) {
      throw TypeError('Cannot initialize #a twice on the same object');
    }
    Object.defineProperty(this, _a, {
      writable: true,
      configurable: false,
      enumerable: false,
      value: 0
    });
    // What the %CreateDataProperty() call roughly translates to:
    Object.defineProperty(this, 'b', {
      writable: true,
      configurable: true,
      enumerable: true,
      value: this[_a]
    });
  }
}
```

