TITLE: Implementing Write Barrier for Incremental Marking in V8
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows the implementation of a Dijkstra-style write barrier in V8. It's called after each write operation to maintain the strong tri-color invariant, ensuring that no black object points to a white object during incremental marking.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/concurrent-marking.md#2025-04-10_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
// Called after `object.field = value`.
write_barrier(object, field_offset, value) {
  if (color(object) == black && color(value) == white) {
    set_color(value, grey);
    marking_worklist.push(value);
  }
}
```

