TITLE: Implementing Int32Add1 for x64 Architecture
DESCRIPTION: This change adds the x64-specific implementation of Int32Add1 in the instruction selector. It emits the kX64Int32Add1 instruction with the appropriate operands, ensuring the output register is the same as the first input register.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/docs/webassembly-opcode.md#2025-04-10_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: diff
CODE:
```
diff --git a/src/compiler/backend/x64/instruction-selector-x64.cc b/src/compiler/backend/x64/instruction-selector-x64.cc
index 2324e119a6..4b55671243 100644
--- a/src/compiler/backend/x64/instruction-selector-x64.cc
+++ b/src/compiler/backend/x64/instruction-selector-x64.cc
@@ -841,6 +841,11 @@ void InstructionSelector::VisitWord32ReverseBytes(Node* node) {
   Emit(kX64Bswap32, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
 }

+void InstructionSelector::VisitInt32Add1(Node* node) {
+  X64OperandGenerator g(this);
+  Emit(kX64Int32Add1, g.DefineSameAsFirst(node), g.UseRegister(node->InputAt(0)));
+}
+
```

