TITLE: Inheritance Behavior of Private Fields in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how private fields are inherited by subclasses as own-properties, but not by objects created with Object.create or prototype manipulation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/features/private-brand-checks.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
class SubA extends A {};
A.test(new SubA()); // true

const a = new A();
const o = Object.create(a);
A.test(o); // false, private field is inherited and not owned
A.test(o.__proto__); // true

const o2 = {};
Object.setPrototypeOf(o2, a);
A.test(o2); // false, private field is inherited and not owned
A.test(o2.__proto__); // true
```

