TITLE: Original Hash Function for Numeric Strings in V8
DESCRIPTION: This C++ code snippet shows the original hash function used for numeric strings in V8's StringsStorage, which was causing performance issues due to collisions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/speeding-up-v8-heap-snapshots.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
int32_t OriginalHash(const std::string& numeric_string) {
  int kValueBits = 24;

  int32_t mask = (1 << kValueBits) - 1; /* 0xffffff */
  return (numeric_string.length() << kValueBits) | (numeric_string & mask);
}
```

