TITLE: Example of Write Barrier with Suboptimal Decompression in C++ and Assembly
DESCRIPTION: An example showing how the compiler fails to optimize decompression operations in a write barrier implementation. The compiler conservatively loads the base pointer in the hot path even though it's only used in the cold path, demonstrating the need for manual optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/oilpan-pointer-compression.md#2025-04-10_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
extern const uint64_t base;
extern std::atomic_bool enabled;

void Assign(uint32_t ptr) {
  ptr_ = ptr
  WriteBarrier(Decompress(ptr));
}

void WriteBarrier(void* ptr) {
  if (LIKELY(
      !enabled.load(relaxed)))
    return;
  SlowPath(ptr);
}
```

