TITLE: Manual SIMD Implementation Using Intrinsics in C++
DESCRIPTION: C++ function that explicitly uses SIMD intrinsics from wasm_simd128.h to multiply array elements in parallel, processing 4 elements at a time.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/features/simd.md#2025-04-10_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: cpp
CODE:
```
#include <wasm_simd128.h>

void multiply_arrays(int* out, int* in_a, int* in_b, int size) {
  for (int i = 0; i < size; i += 4) {
    v128_t a = wasm_v128_load(&in_a[i]);
    v128_t b = wasm_v128_load(&in_b[i]);
    v128_t prod = wasm_i32x4_mul(a, b);
    wasm_v128_store(&out[i], prod);
  }
}
```

