TITLE: Mutual Recursion Example in C with Tail Calls
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of even/odd number checking using mutual recursion with musttail attribute for proper tail call optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/wasm-tail-call.md#2025-04-10_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdbool.h>

bool is_odd(unsigned n);
bool is_even(unsigned n);

bool is_odd(unsigned n) {
  if (n == 0) {
    return false;
  }
  __attribute__((__musttail__))
  return is_even(n - 1);
}

bool is_even(unsigned n) {
  if (n == 0) {
    return true;
  }
  __attribute__((__musttail__))
  return is_odd(n - 1);
}

int main() {
  printf("is_even(1000000): %d\n", is_even(1000000));
}
```

