TITLE: Implementing for-in Loop Mechanics in V8 JavaScript Engine
DESCRIPTION: Pseudo-C++ code demonstrating the three main steps of for-in implementation in V8: preparing keys to iterate over, getting the next key, and evaluating the for-in body. This shows how EnumCache is utilized for optimization.
SOURCE: https://github.com/v8/v8.dev/blob/main/src/blog/fast-for-in.md#2025-04-10_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// For-In Prepare:
FixedArray* keys = nullptr;
Map* original_map = object->map();
if (original_map->HasEnumCache()) {
  if (object->HasNoElements()) {
    keys = original_map->GetCachedEnumKeys();
  } else {
    keys = object->GetCachedEnumKeysWithElements();
  }
} else {
  keys = object->GetEnumKeys();
}

// For-In Body:
for (size_t i = 0; i < keys->length(); i++) {
  // For-In Next:
  String* key = keys[i];
  if (!object->HasProperty(key) continue;
  EVALUATE_FOR_IN_BODY();
}
```

